                <svg class="about_line" width="72vw" viewBox="0 0 2570 929" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <path id="path" class="anim" d="M55.5 88.0002C210.833 194.334 539.9 357.7 1013.5 268.5C1605.5 157 1690.5 -92.9998 2005.5 57.5001C2370.69 231.977 2266.5 570.5 1681.5 586C1096.5 601.5 604.607 267.692 154.5 620.5C-130 843.5 199.5 1036 818.5 832.5C1313.7 669.7 2053 1194 2507 686.5" stroke-width="20" stroke-dasharray="80 80"/>
                </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="modal_overlay">
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[0]} boxLogos={boxLogos[0]} viewBoxSize="0 0 384 512">
                    <p>
                        My journey in web development started 3 years ago, I was discovered HTML5 with page structure, tags and attributes for
                        the first time. Used Sublime Text IDE to create my own pages and added links to join them together. But something was missing, my
                        pages needed styles to look better...
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[1]} boxLogos={boxLogos[1]} viewBoxSize="0 0 384 512">
                    <p>
                        The Cascading Style Sheet Language was create to solve this kind of problem. And just with these 2 languages I was able to create
                        entire websites by myself. This was the time to dive into the web to learn more about all different styles. I could now add colors,
                        shapes, animations and media queries for the responsive design...
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[2]} boxLogos={boxLogos[2]} viewBoxSize="0 0 448 512">
                    <p>
                        Starting directly with the ES6 standard I was not very good for algorithmic language like JS, with these variables, conditions, loops
                        and the oriented object paradigm more globally. Maybe because it was to early, the fact was, I’ve stopped to learn it from this moment.
                        I’ve chosen to focus on other jobs like designer, video editor which were also presented in my courses.
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[3]} boxLogos={boxLogos[3]} viewBoxSize="0 0 576 512">
                    <p>
                        After obtain my associate degree, I couldn’t (and always can’t today) stop to learn by myself. I’ve tried many class courses in
                        web, in many platforms which the most popular was Coursera and Udemy in <a href="https://www.credly.com/users/paul-mallet/badges" target="_blank">Digital Marketing</a> with the Marketing Funnel, SEO/SEM, Social
                        Media Ads, E-mail Marketing and E-commerce integration strategies.
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[4]} boxLogos={boxLogos[4]} viewBoxSize="0 0 576 512">
                    <p>
                    And also in the world of data, with a Google course which introduced how to data analyse by asking good questions, prepare
                    data, process, analyse, share it with stakeholders and act thanks to insights discovered. I’ve used SQL queries to filter and sort
                    datasets, R language to create visualisations and Tableau a visual analytic platform.
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[5]} boxLogos={boxLogos[5]} viewBoxSize="0 0 448 512">
                    <p>
                    But during this time, after done these courses I was always searching for my real passion, and the coding was the response. I’ve
                    never stop to code, even during courses, in HTML,CSS and WordPress but not in JS. It’s a FreeCodeCamp video which illuminates me and let
                    me try again. And I was more self-confident to use it in my projects.
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[6]} boxLogos={boxLogos[6]} viewBoxSize="0 0 448 512">
                    <p>
                    This summer I’ve participated at a 42 pool, like a long hackathon during 4 weeks to improve my skills. It was a grateful experience, I’ve
                    discovered Shell and C language with 200 other pool mates. The C was more longer to learn than JS because it’s low level which means
                    to be careful. But it’s a powerful language due, in part, to the manual memory management.
                    </p>
                </Box>
                <Box boxTitle={boxTitle[7]} boxLogos={boxLogos[7]} viewBoxSize="0 0 512 512">
                    <p>
                    Now, after finished the 42 pool I’ve made some new things in JS again. Like this Portfolio in Astro.js and GSAP. I would
                    definitely become developer and the web will be the first place where I want to work with. To be a frontend engineer at first by
                    using JS frameworks like React to create applications. And maybe one day become a fullstack engineer by using Node.js or Python in backend
                    devices...
                    </p>
                </Box>
            </div>
        </div>
    </Frame>
